### **ğŸ‘ï¸ Vision & Screen Comfort (8 cards)**
1. High Contrast - Hard to see text and buttons
2. Mouse Pointer Size - Lose track of pointer
3. Narrator (Screen Reader) - Blind or very low vision
4. Browser Zoom - Websites too small
5. Reading Guide - Lose place when reading
6. Reduce Motion - Moving content makes dizzy
7. Visual Notifications - Miss notifications
8. Simplify Desktop - Screen overwhelming

### **ğŸ‘‚ Hearing & Communication (8 cards)**
1. Live Captions - Can't hear what people say in videos
2. Teams Captions - Hard to follow online meetings
3. Transcribe - Need written record of meetings
4. Mono Audio - Can only hear from one ear
5. Visual Alerts - Miss notification sounds
6. Audio Balance - One ear hears better
7. Sound Enhancements - Audio not loud enough
8. Sign Language View - Use sign language

### **ğŸ–ï¸ Motor & Physical Access (6 cards)**
1. On-Screen Keyboard - Hard to use physical keyboard
2. Mouse Keys - Hard to use mouse
3. Voice Access - Control computer with voice
4. Eye Control - Control computer with eyes
5. ClickLock - Holding mouse button difficult
6. Filter Keys - Type slowly and make errors

